<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 18 at 5:43AM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>A winter weather advisory is in effect for the higher elevations
north of Interstate 64 today for accumulating snow, sleet, and
freezing rain. Farther south, some mixed precipitation is possible
but little or no accumulation is expected. Higher elevations,
such as the Blue Ridge Parkway north of Roanoke, and ridge tops,
such as Mountain Lake and Peters Mountain, may experience
temperatures near, or just below freezing, allowing for some icing
in the trees. An inch or two of snow and sleet is also possible
for the Wilderness area in northern Amherst County. Roads which
cross these higher elevations may become snow covered or slushy.
Ice accumulation in trees may result in downed tree limbs. If your
travel involves these higher elevations, please use extra
caution.</description>
